On Jan 26, 2004, at 1:04 PM, Eric O'Dell wrote:

> So what is a "CDI box" exactly?

Capacitive Discharge Ignition.

Aircooled.net sells a Mallory HyFire unit for $120-$160 (depending on 
if you want a rev limiter or not):

http://www.aircooled.net/new-bin/viewproductdetail.php?keyword2=IGN0004

CDIs use capacitors to store up and discharge juice that eventually 
makes it to the plugs.  That's about all I can say about them, 
though... I don't really have any idea how they're plumbed into the 
ignition system (although, I am definitely interested in learning more 
about them).

